api/map_or_else.html.body:
map_or_else() [since 1.2.0]
template 
constexpr auto map_or_else(Fallback&& _fallback, Map&& _map) const&
    -> std::common_type_t, std::invoke_result_t>

Maps a Result to U by applying a function to a contained Ok value, or a fallback function to a contained Err value.
This function can be used to unpack a successful result while handling an error.
Examples
Basic usage:
auto k = 21;
{
    Result x = Ok("foo"s);
    assert(x.map_or_else([k](auto){ return k * 2; }, [](auto v) { return v.length(); }) == 3);
}
{
    Result x = Err("bar"s);
    assert(x.map_or_else([k](auto){ return k * 2; }, [](auto v) { return v.length(); }) == 42);
}

